oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Champion Football Team, 1923
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Football; Athletes
oai_dc:dc.dc:description:
The Christian Brothers College championship football team of 1923 finished the season at 11 and 0.
Top Row: Brother Sylvester (coach), McDonnell, Tom Shea, Cummings, Spenser Ellis, Joe Montedonico, Hiliary Linder
Second Row from Top: Speed Lynch, Jack Guine, Powers, Pelegrin, unknown, Kardell Linder
Third Row: unknown, Ernie Marquette, Marion Hale, Pat Johnson, Beverly Wade, George Clawson, unknown, unknown
Fourth Row: Ed Kuhn, Dick Ward, Maury Wade, Manigan, Red Schneider, Bill Clark, Chris Arnoult
Bottom Row: T. Clarke, H. Buggs, unknown, unknown, Charles Walsh, unknown
